  "why": "The paper provides a partial diagnostic insight by analyzing and classifying the discovered failures into distinct patterns. In the case study (RQ4), the authors identify and categorize five types of erroneous behaviors observed in the Question Answering (QA) systems under test. These categories include answering unanswerable questions, failing to answer answerable questions, providing unrelated answers, selecting wrong keywords, and failing at logical reasoning. This analysis successfully characterizes *how* the systems fail by identifying patterns in the erroneous outputs. However, the analysis does not extend to linking these failure patterns to specific, underlying model vulnerabilities such as training data bias, reliance on spurious features, or overfitting. It describes the symptoms of the failures without diagnosing the root cause within the model's architecture or training regimen.",
